l; font-size:12pt"> This has seen quick progress in the past few months with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Clare Short (EITI chairperson) attend</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a meeting in December 2013 which brought government, civil society and companies from the extractive sector around the table for the first time</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. This</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> confirm</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the willingness of these stakeholders to participate in the EITI process. There is a lot of difficult work ahead but this is strong progress given the levels of distrust between these groups in the past.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Launched an expression of interest process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for a £19 million programme over five</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">years to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">increase private sector investment into pro-poor infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in the agriculture sector in Burma. This programme will be run </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Infraco Asia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which is part of Private Infrastructure Development Group</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Agreed focus sectors for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">our £5 million programme over four years to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">work with private sector firms to develop business models that create economic opportunities for poor people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  This is through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Business Innovation Facility</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and the focus sectors are initially g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">arments, tourism</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and fisheries.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Worked with the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Myanmar Centre for Responsible </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Business</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to improve its website and strengthen outreach to the private sector. Progress has also been made on centre’s Impact Assessments in Tourism and Oil and Gas which will be finished this quarter.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Agreed funding of £0.5m </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> International Finance Corporation to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> assist the Burmese Central Bank to develop a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">credit reporting system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Worked with the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Livelihoods and Food Security Trust Fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to identify how it could begin working in new ceasefire areas. We are also working with the Government on its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Rural Development Strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, initiated by the President, which is an unprecedented opportunity to influence their policy in this area. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>